title: Ex-Brazil president's home searched by police probing 'fake COVID vaccine cards'
description: The home of Brazil's ex-president Jair Bolsonaro has been searched by police investigating COVID-19 vaccine cards allegedly being falsified.

title: Cristiano Ronaldo named highest paid athlete, as Forbes reveals the top ten most expensive sports stars
description: Portuguese football star Cristiano Ronaldo has been named the world's highest paid athlete, thanks to a big money move to Saudi Arabia, according to Forbes.

title: Drone attack probably wasn't assassination attempt but you can't blame Russia for making the most of it
description: Whoever flew a drone into the Kremlin knew what they were doing. The footage is spectacular.

title: Iran seizes second oil tanker in a week in 'threat to global economy'
description: Iran has seized a second oil tanker in Gulf waters in a week as tensions with the US increase.

title: Any Russian threat to Eurovision voting will be dealt with, MPs told
description: Threats to voting at the Eurovision song contest in Liverpool from Russian agents or cyber attacks will be dealt with by the UK's security experts, MPs have been assured.

title: Kremlin claims it foiled two drones in 'planned terrorist act' on Putin's residence
description: Russia has claimed it stopped two drone attacks on Vladimir Putin's presidential home overnight.

title: Inside war-torn Sudan where people are trapped in prison of urban warfare
description: Smoky spectres climb up the Khartoum skyline. A pop goes off in the distance and there is a slow rumble of thunder before another pillar builds upwards.

title: The million dollar streets strewn with bodies contorted by the effects of fentanyl
description: Bodies are strewn on the doorstep of San Francisco's main government building, contorted by the effects of fentanyl, a painkiller 100 times more potent than morphine.

title: Boy kills at least one and injures five in Belgrade school shooting
description: A 14-year-old boy shot his teacher before opening fire on other students and security guards in a school shooting in Serbia which has left one dead and five injured, police have said.

title: Russian 'ghost ships' pictured near pipeline explosion site days before blasts
description: Russian navy vessels able to perform underwater operations were present near the sabotaged Nord Stream gas pipelines prior to mysterious blasts in September, according to an investigative documentary.

title: Lionel Messi suspended by PSG for unauthorised trip to Saudi Arabia
description: Lionel Messi has been suspended by Paris Saint-Germain for making a personal promotional trip to Saudi Arabia without the club's permission.

title: Russia's Victory Day celebrations scaled back over fears of attack
description: Security is being beefed up in Moscow and several Russian regions have announced they are scaling back this year's Victory Day celebrations due to fears pro-Ukrainian saboteurs could target the festivities.

title: Stab wounds to heart and lung killed 'brilliant' app founder
description: Cash App founder Bob Lee died during surgery for stab wounds that pierced his heart and a lung.

title: Teenage girl dies after horse knocks her off during contest
description: A teenager has died in Florida after being knocked off her horse during a contest.

title: More than 150 arrested across Europe after investigation into Italy's most powerful mafia group
description: More than 150 people have been arrested across Germany, Spain and Italy after a three-year investigation into a powerful Italian mafia group.

title: 'Fentanyl steals your friends': Pills bought on social media are killing kids in classrooms and in their beds
description: All over America, families are being broken by fentanyl.

title: Remains of fisherman who vanished found inside two crocodiles
description: Human remains of a missing fisherman have been found inside two crocodiles in a remote part of northern Queensland in Australia.
